  "text": "The problem of interest is the sequential detection of the position of a moving target. As a motivating example, a moving ship is considered in the sea, and one observer is located at a fixed point. This is a classical problem in nonlinear tracking (see Gordon et al.[17] , Carpenter et al. [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , and Gilks et al. [CITATION_3] ).",
